<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-76-0935 </DOCNO><TEXT>A sampling system for radioactive ion exchange resins, which are collectedin at least one collecting container and are pumped by a pump using aliquid, has a pipe duct leading to the container, to which the suctionpipe of a solid jet pump is connected. The suction pipe of a liquid pumpis connected to a part of the container separated by a sieve, which suppliesthe liquid for the solid jet pump. The pressure pipe of the solid jetpump leads to the upper part of the container and a sample vessel isarranged parallel with it.</TEXT></DOC>